or agents.\\n\\n**Compared to general README files**, AGENTS.md complements README.md by containing the extra, sometimes detailed context coding agents need: build steps, tests, and conventions that might clutter a README or aren't relevant to human contributors.\\n\\n## File Precedence and Location\\n\\nOpenCode follows a specific precedence order when looking for instruction files: Project rules can be CLAUDE.md in your project directory (used if no AGENTS.md exists), and the first matching file wins in each category—if you have both AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md, only AGENTS.md is used.\\n\\nYou can create an AGENTS.md file by running the /init command in opencode, and you should commit your project's AGENTS.md file to Git.\\n\\n## Related to OPENCODE.md\\n\\nThe search results primarily discuss AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md files rather than an \\\"OPENCODE.md\\\" file specifically. However, for monorepos or projects with shared standards, using opencode.json with glob patterns (like packages/*/AGENTS.md) is more maintainable than manual instructions.\\n\\nThe framework supports having multiple AGENTS.md files in different locations for hierarchical instruction management across projects and teams.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"310d68a2-8283-4485-96f0-4e36c92c2140\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-24T12:08:40.949Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"query\":\"OpenCode AI agent OPENCODE.md vs AGENT.md project instructions 2025 2026\",\"results\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"srvtoolu_014cA3zMiTnAvTQJwPqN9EbL\",\"content\":[{\"title\":\"Rules | OpenCode\",\"url\":\"https://opencode.ai/docs/rules/\"},{\"title\":\"Agents | OpenCode\",\"url\":\"https://opencode.ai/docs/agents/\"},{\"title\":\"Agent Skills | OpenCode\",\"url\":\"https://opencode.ai/docs/skills/\"},{\"title\":\"Custom instructions with AGENTS.md\",\"url\":\"https://developers.openai.com/codex/guides/agents-md/\"},{\"title\":\"Intro | AI coding agent b